ENTRY       EC 4.2.3.74                 Enzyme
NAME        presilphiperfolanol synthase;
            BcBOT2, CND15
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Acting on phosphates
SYSNAME     (2E,6E)-farnesyl-diphosphate diphosphohydrolase (presilphiperfolan-8beta-ol-forming)
REACTION    (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate + H2O = presilphiperfolan-8beta-ol + diphosphate [RN:R09630]
ALL_REAC    R09630
SUBSTRATE   (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate [CPD:C00448];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     presilphiperfolan-8beta-ol [CPD:C19756];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     Requires Mg2+. Presilphiperfolan-8beta-ol is the precursor of botrydial, a phytotoxic sesquiterpene metabolite secreted by the fungus Botryotinia fuckeliana (Botrytis cinerea), the causal agent of gray mold disease in plants.
